**Example:**
```css
div {
  width: 300px;
  padding: 25px;
  border: 5px solid black;
  margin: 25px;
}
```

**Box Sizing:**
```css
/* Default: content-box */
div {
  box-sizing: content-box;
  /* width = content width only */
}

/* Recommended: border-box */
div {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  /* width includes padding and border */
}
```

Control space around and inside elements.

**Margin (Outside Space):**
```css
/* All sides */
div {
  margin: 25px;
}

/* Individual sides */
div {
  margin-top: 50px;
  margin-right: 30px;
  margin-bottom: 50px;
  margin-left: 30px;
}

/* Shorthand: top right bottom left */
div {
  margin: 50px 30px 50px 30px;
}

/* Shorthand: top/bottom left/right */
div {
  margin: 50px 30px;
}
```

**Padding (Inside Space):**
```css
div {
  padding: 20px;
  padding: 10px 20px 10px 20px;
}
```

**Auto Margin (Centering):**
```css
div {
  width: 300px;
  margin: 0 auto; /* Centers horizontally */
}
```

The display property controls how elements are displayed.

**Common Display Values:**
```css
/* Block-level elements */
div {
  display: block;
  /* Takes full width, starts on new line */
}

/* Inline elements */
span {
  display: inline;
  /* Only takes needed width, stays in line */
}

/* Inline-block */
div {
  display: inline-block;
  /* Inline but can have width/height */
}

/* None (hides element) */
div {
  display: none;
  /* Element is hidden, takes no space */
}
```

**Flexbox:**
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
}
```

**Grid:**
```css
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
}
```

Control element positioning on the page.

**Position Values:**
```css
/* Static (default) */
div {
  position: static;
}

/* Relative (relative to normal position) */
div {
  position: relative;
  top: 10px;
  left: 20px;
}

/* Absolute (relative to nearest positioned parent) */
div {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50px;
  right: 100px;
}

/* Fixed (relative to viewport) */
div {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 0;
  right: 0;
}

/* Sticky (scrolls until threshold) */
div {
  position: sticky;
  top: 10px;
}
```

**Z-Index (Stacking Order):**
```css
div {
  position: absolute;
  z-index: 10; /* Higher = on top */
}
```

Control how content that exceeds element bounds is handled.

**Overflow Property:**
```css
/* Visible (default) */
div {
  overflow: visible;
}

/* Hidden (clip content) */
div {
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* Scroll (add scrollbars) */
div {
  overflow: scroll;
}

/* Auto (scroll when needed) */
div {
  overflow: auto;
}

/* Individual axes */
div {
  overflow-x: hidden;
  overflow-y: scroll;
}
```

**Visibility:**
```css
div {
  visibility: visible; /* default */
  visibility: hidden; /* hidden but takes space */
}

/* Difference from display: none */
/* display: none - element removed from layout */
/* visibility: hidden - element invisible but in layout */
```
